## Question 25

C varies as the cube root of D and D
$=125$ when $\mathrm{C}=2$. Find C when $\mathrm{D}=8$

## Solution

$$
\begin{aligned}
& \text { C } \alpha \frac{1}{\sqrt[3]{D}} \\
& 2=\frac{k}{\sqrt[3]{D}} \\
& 2=\frac{k}{\sqrt[3]{125}} \\
& 2=\frac{k}{5}
\end{aligned}
$$

$$
\begin{aligned}
& 2 \times 5=\mathrm{k} \therefore \quad \underline{\mathrm{k}=10} \\
& \mathrm{C}=\frac{10}{\sqrt[3]{D}} \\
& \mathrm{C}=\frac{10}{\sqrt[3]{8}} \\
& \mathrm{C}=\frac{10}{2}
\end{aligned}
$$

